@Situation:	Home Visit 7
@Activities:	Magnet activity
@Comment:	Chi and Bro are playing with the magnets simultaneously , but separately. In order for this transcript to be comprehensible , only Chi's activities with the magnets are recorded , except in places when Chi and Bro are interacting. The transcript JAKET7.TXT has Bro's interaction with the magnets , and the transcript FULLET7.TXT has both children's interactions recorded simultaneously (but it is very hard to follow)
@Types:	long, toyplay, TD
*CHI:	what's this ?
%mor:	pron|what-Int-S1 pron|this-Dem-S1 ?
%gra:	1|0|ROOT 2|1|NSUBJ 3|1|PUNCT
@Comment:	Time is 37:34
@Comment:	Chi , Chi's twin Bro , and Mot are present at this activity. Chi and Bro play independently of each other , interacting rarely. Chi experiments with how high he can build towers. A large proportion of Chi's speech is to himself , mainly thinking out loud or describing what he does as he does it. At one point , MOT mistakes a metal piece for a magnet , and Chi shows her that it's only the pieces' indirect connection with the strength of the magnetic base which allows them to stick together. A couple of times , Chi engages in fantasy play. Although Chi interacts very little with the other people in the room , the interactions he does have are generally cheerful and pleasant , although at one point he does emphatically correct Mot when she describes the boys' art projects to EXP incorrectly. Videotape does not start until later , up until that point transcript is from audio tape only
